 806:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_spi.c ****     This subsection provides a set of functions allowing to manage the SPI
 807:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_spi.c ****     data transfers.
 808:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_spi.c **** 
 809:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_spi.c ****     [..] The SPI supports master and slave mode :
 810:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_spi.c **** 
 811:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_spi.c ****     (#) There are two modes of transfer:
 812:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_spi.c ****        (##) Blocking mode: The communication is performed in polling mode.
 813:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_spi.c ****             The HAL status of all data processing is returned by the same function
 814:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_spi.c ****             after finishing transfer.
 815:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_spi.c ****        (##) No-Blocking mode: The communication is performed using Interrupts
 816:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_spi.c ****             or DMA, These APIs return the HAL status.
 817:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_spi.c ****             The end of the data processing will be indicated through the
 818:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_spi.c ****             dedicated SPI IRQ when using Interrupt mode or the DMA IRQ when
 819:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_spi.c ****             using DMA mode.
 820:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_spi.c ****             The HAL_SPI_TxCpltCallback(), HAL_SPI_RxCpltCallback() and HAL_SPI_TxRxCpltCallback() u
 821:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_spi.c ****             will be executed respectively at the end of the transmit or Receive process
 822:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_spi.c ****             The HAL_SPI_ErrorCallback()user callback will be executed when a communication error is
 823:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_spi.c **** 
 824:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_spi.c ****     (#) APIs provided for these 2 transfer modes (Blocking mode or Non blocking mode using either I
 825:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_spi.c ****         exist for 1Line (simplex) and 2Lines (full duplex) modes.
 826:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_spi.c **** 
 827:Drivers/STM32H5xx_HAL_Driver/Src/stm32h5xx_hal_spi.c **** @endverbatim
